<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>POWER STEERING GEAR: SHEPPARD M-SERIES - TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="x0501502">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>This section is designed to give you causes and possible remedies for the most common symptoms. Three
                columns which give the Symptom, Possible Cause, and Remedy are listed.
            </para>
            <table id="t0501509">
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.97in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.19in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="2.34in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Symptom</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Possible Cause</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Remedy</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Oil leaking at output shaft of steering gear.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Damaged sector shaft seal.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Replace sector shaft seal.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="1">
                                <para>Oil leaking at actuating shaft of steering gear.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Worn or damaged oil seal.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Replace actuating shaft seal.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. Damaged actuating shaft seal surface.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Replace bearing cap, actuating shaft assembly.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="2">
                                <para>Oil leaking at supply pump drive shaft.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Damaged oil seal.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Replace oil seal.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. Oil seal heat damaged.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Check operating temperature.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>3. Loose or damaged bushing on pump.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>3. Repair pump per pump service instruction.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Lubricant milky or white in appearance.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Water entry through reservoir venting system.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Clean vent system or replace cap assembly.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="5">
                                <para>Oil forced out of reservoir or foaming.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Clogged oil filter.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Change oil and oil filter.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. Air in system.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Bleed air from system. Check for air leak on suction side of supply pump.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>3. Relief plungers of steering gear not adjusted properly creating high operating
                                    temperatures.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>3. Adjust relief plungers. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s05015y_X0501506.xml" xrefid="x0501506">SET RELIEF PLUNGERS.
                                    </hotlnk>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>4. Air leak in suction side of supply pump.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>4. Refer to pump servicing instructions in GROUP 05 - STEERING in the CTS-5000
                                    Master Service Manual.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>5. Pump cavitating.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>5 . Check for restriction in pump supply.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>6. Oil overheating.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>6. Check for restriction in steering gear return.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="1">
                                <para>Engine oil in power steering reservoir (gear driven pump).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Faulty seal at pump drive shaft.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Repair pump.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. Faulty seal at accessory shaft driving supply pump.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Repair accessory.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="1">
                                <para>Lubricating oil discolored or smells bad.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Operating temperatures too high.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Check and correct cause of overheating. Change intervals may be too long. Refer
                                    to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for type of steering
                                    fluid and change intervals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. Incorrect lubricant used.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Drain, flush and refill with recommended fluid.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="1">
                                <para>High operating temperatures.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Oil flow restriction.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Increase oil flow.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. Oil flow too high.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Check maximum oil flow.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>No power steering on cold starting.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Hydraulic supply pump vanes not extending (vane type pump only).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Increase engine speed momentarily to extend vanes and start pump action.
                                    Usually does not happen often and does not last long. Not a cause for pump repair or
                                    replacement.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="1">
                                <para>Excessive pump pressure with steering gear in neutral position.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Pinched oil return line.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Relocate line.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. High back pressure. Binding steering column.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Repair steering column.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Wheel cuts restricted.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Relief plungers not adjusted properly.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Adjust relief plungers. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s05015y_X0501506.xml" xrefid="x0501506">SET RELIEF PLUNGERS.
                                    </hotlnk>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="1">
                                <para>Erratic steering or mechanical steering only.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Insufficient volume of oil.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Refer to pump servicing instructions. Refer to GROUP 05-STEERING in the
                                    CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. Sticking pressure relief valve in steering gear.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Repair or replace relief valve as required.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="2">
                                <para>Hard Steering.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Faulty supply pump.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Check pump flow.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. Steering out of alignment.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Align front end.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>3. High operating temperature.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>3. Locate and correct cause of overheating.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="5">
                                <para>Wheel turns hard in one or both directions.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Dirt or foreign matter trapped in piston relief.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Check pressure relief.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. Bent or damaged king pins and tie rods.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Repair or replace king pins and tie rods.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>3. Front end load too great.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>3. Lighten load.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>4. Low oil level in steering system.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>4. Fill oil reservoir as required.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>5. Air in system.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>5. Bleed system and check for cause of air.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>6. Caster degree incorrect.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>6. Correct to specifications.*</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Wheel turns hard in one direction.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Metal or foreign material in relief ball seat in piston of steering gear.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Remove and clean relief valve seats or replace damaged parts.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="4">
                                <para>No attempt to return straight ahead from turns - should also be hard steering
                                    complaint.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. No positive caster.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Set caster.*</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. Steering column bind.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Check and repair U-joints and support bearings.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>3. Steering gear mounting distorted.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>3. Shim mounting pads to correct piston to bore interference. Make sure correct
                                    bolt length is used on the base mount gears.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>4. Linkage ball sockets seized or binding.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>4. Check and repair or replace.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>5. King pins seized or binding.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>5. Repair or replace. Refer to GROUP 05 - STEERING in the CTS-5000 Master Service
                                    Manual.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="6">
                                <para>Darting, wandering (steering).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Oil flow too high.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Supply pump not to specifications. Refer to GROUP 05 - STEERING in the CTS-5000
                                    Master Service Manual.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. Air trapped in steering gear.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Bleed system.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>3. Looseness, worn front end parts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>3. Check and repair as required.*</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>4. Front end alignment not correct.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>4. Align front end caster.*</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>5. Overloading.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>5. Reduce loads.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>6. Rear axle not parallel.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>6. Check and repair as required. Refer to GROUP 03 - SUSPENSION in the CTS-5000
                                    Master Service Manual.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>7. Tight tie rod ends and drag link sockets.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>7. Check rotational torque and replace if necessary.*</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="6">
                                <para>Excessive backlash/freeplay.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Worn universal joint.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Replace universal joint. Refer to GROUP 05 - STEERING COLUMN in the CTS-5000
                                    Master Service Manual.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. Worn pins and keys in universal joint to actuating shaft and universal joint to
                                    steering shaft.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Replace pins and keys.*</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>3. Pitman arm ball worn "egg-shaped" (if equipped).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>3. Replace pitman arm assembly where riveted ball is used.*</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>4. Rack on piston damaged.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>4. Replace steering gear.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>5. Damaged sector shaft/ splines.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>5. Replace steering gear.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>6. Worn or damaged pitman arm splines.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>6. Replace pitman arm and/or sector shaft.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>7. Universal joint yoke loose on actuating shaft.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>7. Repair or replace damaged parts.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="5">
                                <para>Steering input not smooth.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1. Worn universal joint.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>1. Check and replace as required.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2. Lack of lubrication.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>2. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for
                                    lubrication information.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>3. Low oil flow.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>3. Idle speed too slow. Drive belts slipping.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>4. Pump cavitating.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>4. Correct pump supply.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>5. Overheating.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>5. Correct cause of overheating.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>6. Universal joints not phased properly.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>6. Re-phase columns. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s05015y_X0501508.xml" xrefid="x0501508">RE-PHASING COLUMN</hotlnk>
                                    .
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>*Refer to GROUP 02 - FRONT AXLE in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
